This is exactly the issue! Both `GetAuthorIDByID`, `GetUser`, and `SetDefaultName` have the same name for parameter and return column, and they don't use a separate local variable. The generated code reuses the function parameter variable for scanning.

Now let me understand the fix. The template currently has:

```
{{- if or (ne .Arg.Pair .Ret.Pair) (ne .Arg.DefineType .Ret.DefineType) }}
var {{.Ret.Name}} {{.Ret.Type}}
{{- end}}
```

The condition checks if `Arg.Pair` (e.g., `email string`) differs from `Ret.Pair` (e.g., `email string`) OR if `Arg.DefineType` differs from `Ret.DefineType`. When they match, the `var` declaration is skipped, and the function parameter is reused - which is the bug.

The fix should always declare a separate local variable. Let me look at both templates more carefully:

